event.title: 1866, it was part of Plymouth Township, established

data.event: Prior to its incorporation in 1866, it was part of Plymouth Township, established in 1769 by the Susquehanna Company and claimed by Connecticut based on the charter of that colony.

event.title: the past, the chief products of its industrial establishments included

data.event: In the past, the chief products of its industrial establishments included mining drilling machines, miners' squibs, silk hosiery, and lumber products.
